Here’s a simple, clean starter repository structure + basic OAuth2 flow scaffold you can use for a GitHub + Genesys Cloud integration. This is intentionally minimal so you can wire in your own client ID/secret and adjust flows (client credentials vs implicit vs auth code).
________________________________________
📁 Recommended Repo Structure
genesys-oauth-demo/
│
├── public/
│   ├── index.html          # Main UI
│   ├── styles.css          # Optional styling
│   └── app.js              # Front-end OAuth logic
│
├── server/
│   ├── server.js           # Node backend to proxy token exchange
│   └── config.js           # Config (client ID, secret, region)
│
├── .env                    # Secrets (never commit)
├── package.json
└── README.md
________________________________________
🔑 Key Concept (Important for Genesys)
•	Genesys Cloud OAuth requires token exchange on a backend (for Authorization Code flow)
•	You should NOT expose client secret in frontend
•	So: 
o	index.html → login button + redirect handler
o	server.js → exchanges code → access_token
